@6004   = ~Prepare this cantrip~
@6005   = ~Choose a different cantrip~
@6006   = ~Rabbit~
@6007   = ~Scary Ogre Berserker!~
@6008   = ~Prepare Cantrips~
@6009   = ~Cantrips represent a wizard's smallest and most basic spellcasting ability. This allows a spellcaster to prepare several of the following cantrips:
- Drowse
- Vicious Mockery
- Thorn Grasp
- Gust
- Dazzle
- Minor Illusion
- Deflective Shell
- Spell Thrust
- Rigor Mortis
- Wisplight
- Conjure Rabbit
- Armor
- Magic Bolt
- Glimpse
- Diviner's Eyes
- Chaotic Orb
~
@6010   = ~Cantrip Wand~
@6011   = ~When wizards first learn to use magic, before deciding whether to specialize, they are taught some of the most basic and minor effects from each school. Unable as yet to cast proper spells, they channel these cantrips through a wand. A crutch, to be sure, but it has the benefit of not requiring memorization and not running out of charges.

A wizard may use a Cantrip Wand as a ranged weapon, casting a Magic Bolt at an enemy once per round, which does 1d4+1 magic damage. (Note, while doing so the wizard will be at a tactical disadvantage against nearby attackers using melee weapons.) Alternatively, the wizard can use the wand to cast one of the following cantrips:
- Deflective Shell: blocks one 1st- through 3rd level spell targeting the wizard. The Shell last 3 rounds.
- Conjure Rabbit: conjures a small rodent near the wizard, which lasts for 3 rounds.
- Glimpse: gives the wizard a brief (2-second) look at another area of the map.
- Drowse: the target will fall asleep for 1 round on a failed save vs. Spells.
- Bedazzle: the target suffers a -1 penalty to thac0 and AC for 1 round; on a failed save vs. Breath, the penalties are doubled and last for 2 rounds, and the target is blinded for the first round.
- Stiffen Bones: the target suffers from painful stiffness, suffering a -1 penalty to thac0 and damage for 1 round; on a failed save vs. Death, the penalties are doubled and last for 2 rounds, and the target is Slowed for the first round.
- Earthen Grasp: the target will be entangled, unable to move, for 2 rounds on a failed save vs. Petrification.~
@6013   = ~Drowse~
@6014   = ~Drowse

Level: 0
Range: 20 feet
Duration: 3 rounds
Area of Effect: Target
Saving Throw: vs. Spells

This cantrip causes the target to drift off into a very brief slumber, slumping to the ground for 3 rounds before regaining full consciousness.
~
@6015   = ~Vicious Mockery~
@6016   = ~Vicious Mockery

Level: 0
Range: 30 feet
Duration: 3 rounds
Area of Effect: one target
Saving Throw: vs Spells

This cantrip sends intrusive and maddening thoughts into the target's mind. The target will pause for 2 seconds to try and resist the spell's wild urges; then, if they fail a saving throw vs. Spells, the target will go berserk for 3 rounds, wildly attacking the nearest creature whether it be friend or foe.
~
@6017   = ~Thorn Grasp~
@6018   = ~Thorn Grasp

Level: 0
Range: 30 feet
Duration: 2 rounds
Area of Effect: Target
Saving Throw: vs. Breath

This cantrip causes tendrils to rise up from the ground and grab at the target's legs and body, preventing movement for a few seconds. On a failed saving throw vs. Breath Weapon, the target will be held in place for 2 rounds.
~
@6019   = ~Gust~
@6020   = ~Gust

Level: 0
Range: 30 feet
Duration: 1 round
Area of Effect: one target
Saving Throw: vs. Breath

This cantrip creates a sudden strong breeze that blows the target 10 feet away from the caster if they fail a saving throw vs. Breath Weapon with a 2-point penalty. Further, if they fail the saving throw with a 2-point bonus, the target will lose their footing and fall down.
~
@6021   = ~Dazzle~
@6022   = ~Dazzle

Level: 0
Range: 10 feet
Duration: 2 rounds
Area of Effect: Target
Saving Throw: vs. Spells

This cantrip creates intense sparkling light that flash in front of the target's eyes, causing a 2-point penalties to attack rolls for 3 rounds. Further, if the target fails a saving throw vs. spells, they are also blinded for two rounds.
~
@6023   = ~Minor Illusion~
@6024   = ~Minor Illusion

Level: 0
Range: 20 feet
Duration: 3 rounds
Area of Effect: special
Saving Throw: none

This cantrip creates the image of a fearsome ogre at the location of the caster's choosing. This ogre cannot actually harm anyone, and contact with it will dispel the illusion. In the right situation, this can be very valuable as a momentary distraction.
~
@6025   = ~Reflected Image~
@6026   = ~Reflected Image

Level: 0
Range: 0
Duration: 4 rounds
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

This cantrip creates an image of <PRO_HIMHER>self that travels alongside <PRO_HIMHER>. A successful attacker has a 50% chance to strike the image (which then disappears) and a 50% chance to strike the caster.
~
@6027   = ~Deflective shell~
@6028   = ~Deflective shell

Level: 0
Range: 0
Duration: 5 rounds
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

This cantrip raises a fragile magical barrier around the caster. This thin shell of energy will absorb the effects of a single spell of up to 3rd level that is directed at the caster.
~
@6029   = ~Spell Thrust~
@6030   = ~Spell Thrust

Level: 0
Range: 30 ft.
Duration: instant
Area of Effect: one target
Saving Throw: none

This cantrip will dispel spell protections of 5th level and lower. This includes: Minor Spell Deflection, Minor Globe of Invulnerability, Spell Immunity, and Minor Spell Turning.
~
@6031   = ~Rigor  Mortis~
@6032   = ~Rigor  Mortis

Level: 0
Range: 20 feet
Duration: 3 rounds
Area of Effect: one target
Saving Throw: vs. Death

This cantrip the target's body to ache and stiffen, Slowing the target for 1 round and, on a failed saving throw vs Death, also causing 3-point penalties to Strength, Dexterity, thac0, and AC for 3 rounds.
~
@6033   = ~Wisplight~
@6034   = ~Wisplight

Level: 0
Range: 30 feet
Duration: 3 rounds
Area of Effect: one target
Saving Throw: none

This cantrip causes tiny motes of light to coalesce and swirl around the target. This makes <PRO_HIMHER> easier to strike (2-point penalty to AC) and prevents <PRO_HIMHER> from turning invisible for 3 rounds.
~
@6035   = ~Conjure Rabbit~
@6036   = ~Conjure Rabbit

Level: 0
Range: 20 feet
Duration: 3 rounds
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None

This cantrip conjures a medium-sized bunny in the location of the caster's choosing.
~
@6037   = ~Armor~
@6038   = ~Armor

Level: 0
Range: 0
Duration: 9 hours
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

This cantrip creates a magical protection that is something like scale mail armor (AC 6). The magical Armor does not hinder movement, adds no weight or encumbrance, and doesn't prevent spellcasting.
~
@6039   = ~Magic Bolt~
@6040   = ~Magic Bolt

Level: 0
Range: 30 feet
Duration: n/a
Area of Effect: one target
Saving Throw: none

This cantrip allows the caster to direct a small ball of magical energy at a target, functioning as a once-per round ranged attack that almost never misses. The energy will cause 1d4+1 damage each time it strikes someone. However, it is completely blocked the Shield spell as well as by any magical protection such as Globe of Invulnerability or Spell Deflection.
~
@6041   = ~Glimpse~
@6042   = ~Glimpse

Level: 0
Range: map
Duration: 2 seconds
Area of Effect: special
Saving Throw: none

This cantrip gives the caster a brief (2-second) look at what is happening in another area of the local map.
~
@6043   = ~Diviner's Eyes~
@6044   = ~Diviner's Eyes

Level: 0
Range: 20 feet
Duration: 5 rounds
Area of Effect: one ally
Saving Throw: none

This cantrip allows the caster to share <PRO_HISHER> perspective with an ally - literally. Able to evaluate and process the battlefield from both the caster's perspective and their own, the recipient of this cantrip gains a 2-point bonus on to-hit rolls for 5 rounds.
~
@6045   = ~Chaos Orb~
@6046   = ~Chaos Orb

Level: 0
Range: 30 ft.
Duration: Special
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Special

This spell causes a colorful sphere to speed unerringly to its target. The color and effect as it flies through the air; the effects on the target are unpredictable and include damage as well as a secondary effect which occurs on a failed save vs. Spella with a +2 bonus
 20% chance: 1d4 magic damage and blinds the target for 1 round.
 20% chance: 1d4 acid damage and inflicts pain (-1 penalty to Strength, Dexterity, AC, and THAC0) upon the target for 3 rounds.
 20% chance: 1d4 lightning damage and stuns the target for 1 round.
 20% chance: 1d4 cold damage and causes weakness (-4 penalty to THAC0) in the target for 3 rounds.
 20% chance: 1d4 fire damage and causes the target to panic for 2 rounds.
~
@6091   = ~Cancel Magic Bolt~
