@8004  = ~Find Familiar
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Level: 1
Range: n/a
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 1 familiar
Saving Throw: None

This spell enables the caster to summon a familiar to act as <PRO_HISHER> aide and companion. Familiars are typically small creatures. A creature acting as a familiar can benefit a wizard, conveying its sensory powers to its master, conversing with <PRO_HIMHER>, and serving as a guard, scout, or spy. A wizard can have only one familiar at a time, and <PRO_HESHE> has no control over what sort of creature answers the summoning, if any come at all.

The wizard has an empathic link with the familiar and can issue it mental commands. The creature is always more intelligent than others of its type (typically by 2 or 3 Intelligence points). Its bond with the wizard confers upon it an exceptionally long life and prevents it from truly dying. If the familiar should 'die' in combat the caster may cast Find Familiar again a day later to re-summon it.

At 1st level, all familiars share the following characteristics: 9 hit points, AC 4, thac0 17, saving throws 16, 25% magic and damage resistance, immunity to level drain and petrification. At certain experience thresholds - 5,000 / 50,000 / 150,000 / 450,000 / 1,250,000 / 2,500,000 / 4,000,000 - the familiar's hit points, AC, thac0 and saving throws will improve.

Here is a list of the familiars that the player may choose:

Pseudo Dragon
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d3 damage; save or be Slowed for 2 rounds
- Special Abilities: can cast Blur and Cure Light Wounds, and use a Color Spray breath weapon, once every 3 turns.
- Special Benefit: the pseudodragon's summoner has a 10% higher total hit point total, and regenerates 1 hit point per round.

Ferret
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d3 damage
- Special Abilities: has 80% Pick Pockets score. Can emit a small aura of Nauseating Stench once per turn. For five rounds, enemies near the ferret must save or suffer 2-point penalties to hit and AC and a 30% chance of casting failure.
- Special Benefit: the ferret's summoner has a 10% higher total hit point total, and has a +1 bonus to Constitution.

Rabbit
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d2 damage
- Special Abilities: has 80% Detect Traps score. Can burrow into the ground to escape danger - similar to the Shadowstep ability - once per turn.
- Special Benefit: the rabbit's summoner has a 10% higher total hit point total, and is immune to Slow effects.

Cat
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d3 damage
- Special Abilities: has 99% in Move Silently/Hide in Shadows, and is Nondetectable (as the spell) to magic divinations.
- Special Benefit: the cat's summoner has a 10% higher total hit point total, and has a +1 bonus to Dexterity.

Spider
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d2 damage; save or take 3 poison damage over 1 round
- Special Abilities: can cast a single-target Web, which can tangle the target for 3 rounds, once per 5 rounds.
- Special Benefit: the spider's summoner has a 10% higher total hit point total, and has an extra chance to resist being affected by poisons.

Rat
- Combat: 1 attack per round for 1d2 damage; save or be diseased for 3 rounds, with reduced Strength and a 30% chance of casting failure
- Special Abilities: can summon a cohort of 1d6 more rats to defend it, once per 3 turns.
- Special Benefit: the rat's summoner has a 10% higher total hit point total, and has a +1 bonus to Intelligence.
~
@8011  = ~Pseudodragon~
@8012  = ~Pseudodragon: this is a tiny, distant relative of full dragons. The pseudodragon can cast Cure Light Wounds, and Blur, and use a colorful 'breath weapon' that mimics the Color Spray spell, once every 3 turns. (At high levels, the Blur improves to a full Improved Invisibility effect.) They can attack twice per round and while their claws are small, they deliver a mild intoxicant which can render the target drowsy and clumsy (mimicking the effects of a Slow spell, for two rounds). 

While this familiar is near its master, the summoner regenerates 1 hit point per round.

As pseudodragons can fly, they are impervious to the effects of Grease, Entangle, Web, and similar spells. As with all familiars, their magical connection to the life force of their master renders them immune to petrification and level drain effects.
~
